heaviest_rainfall.status: Ranked 7th for total rainfall, today's storm had precipitation totalling 23.86mm, falling at 8.3mm per hour at times during the 31.0 hour long storm.  Record-breaking rain fell on 09 November 2025 with a total accumulation of 47.89mm over 144.8 hours and falling at a rate of 24.6mm per hour at times.

heaviest_rainrate.status: The rain rate reached 27.6mm per hour during the storm today (ranking 2nd from our records) and resulted in 5.63mm of total rain in 2.1 hours.  34.3mm per hour is the maximum rain rate ever recorded on 02 September 2025, during a 15.0 hour storm which dumped 21.19mm of rain from the clouds.

longest_rain.status: Rain fell for 31.0 hours on 09 November 2025 (ranking 7th from our records for the longest storm) and it produced a total of 23.86mm of rain at a maximum intensity of 8.3mm per hour.  The longest rain storm on record lasted 144.8 hours on 09 November 2025 when 47.89mm of rain fell and at one point was falling at 24.6mm per hour.
